						<summary>

						<p>Slab lying by the side of the well in the Brahmasthāna temple.</p>						

						<p>(Dēvarāya II), 1443-44 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This badly damaged record dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1[366] (current), Rudhirōdgāri</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">1443-44 A.D.,</hi> all other details being lost.</p>						

						<p>It refers to gift of lands probably to a temple, appears to be the village Simantūru. Kōṭinātha sēnabōva appears to be recipient of the gift.</p>						

						</summary>
